'''詹姆斯·亚历山大·沃森'''（{{lang|en|James Alexander "Jim" Watson}}，{{bd|1961年|7月30日}}），[[加拿大|加拿大]]政治人物，[[安大略省|安大略省]][[渥太华|渥太华]]市现任市长，2010年12月1日上任。他曾于1991年-97年間出任渥太華市議員，1997年-2000年间則任該市市长。他其後投身安大略省級政治，2003年-10年間以[[安大略自由黨|安大略自由黨]]黨員身份出任[[安大略省議會|安大略省議會]]渥太華西－尼皮安選區議員，並曾在[[安大略省省長|省長]][[道爾頓·麥堅迪|麥堅迪]]內閣中先後出任消費者及商業事務廳長（2003年-05年）、衞生推廣廳長（2005年-07年）和城鎮事務及房屋廳長（2007年-10年）。

==早年生活==
吉姆·沃森生于[[魁北克省|魁北克省]][[蒙特利尔|蒙特利尔]]市<ref name="WhoWho"/>，在該省西南部拉許特（{{lang|fr|Lachute}}）成長。因應父親工作所需，他童年時期隨家人遷居國內數處，包括魁省比肯斯菲爾德（{{lang|fr|Beaconsfield}}）以及[[安大略省|安省]][[康山_(安大略省)|康山]]和[[薩尼亞市|薩尼亞]]。他從薩尼亞的北方高中畢業<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/ottawa/mayor-ottawa-candidates-election-1.4850095|title=Meet your candidates for Ottawa mayor|date=October 9, 2018|website=www.cbc.ca|access-date=2019-08-17|archive-date=2018-12-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181224022247/https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/ottawa/mayor-ottawa-candidates-election-1.4850095|dead-url=no}}</ref>，後遷居[[渥太華|渥太華]]並在該市的[[卡尔顿大学|卡尔顿大学]]就讀，大學第二年出任麗都河學生宿舍協會主席<ref>{{cite web|title=Jim Watson|url=https://carleton.ca/fpa/story/jim-watson/|website=Carleton University|accessdate=23 January 2018|archive-date=2020-10-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201024210115/https://carleton.ca/fpa/story/jim-watson/|dead-url=no}}</ref>，1983年從該校公共事務学院取得大眾傳播文學士學位<ref>{{cite web|title=Great Grads|url=https://alumni.carleton.ca/grads/watson-jim/|website=Carleton Alumni|accessdate=23 January 2018|archive-date=2018-01-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180109064957/https://alumni.carleton.ca/grads/watson-jim/|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。他畢業後曾在安省數份本地報章工作，後則投身聯邦政府出任公務員，陸續晉升至[[加拿大國會下議院議長|國會下議院議長]]的通訊總監<ref name="Citizen121006">{{cite news |title=Mayor Jim Watson: Married to being mayor |url=http://www.ottawacitizen.com/news/Mayor+Watson+Married+being+mayor/7351500/story.html |newspaper=《渥太華公民報》 |accessdate=2020-10-29 |date=2012-10-06 |first=David |last=Reevely |archive-date=2020-11-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201106133243/http://www.ottawacitizen.com/news/Mayor+Watson+Married+being+mayor/7351500/story.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

==涉足市政==
剛在渥太華舊南區購入一間半獨立屋的沃森有感市府徵收的物業稅項高昂，而他亦對政客向選民信口開河的行爲感到厭倦，因此決意投身市政。他於1991年渥太華市選中競逐首都市選區（{{lang|en|Capital Ward}}）市議員席位並告當選，首度出任民選公職<ref name="Citizen121006"/>。他出任市議員後倡議市府減低薪金及其他營運開支，並於1992年將其爲數700元的市議員薪金增幅捐贈予慈善機構<ref>''Ottawa Citizen'', July 13, 1992.</ref>。他於1994年市選中連任首都市選區議員，並自願削減其市議員薪金13%<ref name="OLM">{{cite web|title=Elementary, Watson!|url=https://www.ottawalife.com/article/elementary-watson|publisher=''Ottawa Life''|accessdate=2020-10-29|date=2017-01-16}}</ref>。1997年市選他改為競逐市長並以82%得票率當選，年屆36歲的沃森遂成為渥太華歷來最年輕市長<ref name="about">{{cite web|title=About Jim|url=https://jimwatsonottawa.ca/en/about-jim/|website=吉姆·沃森個人網站|accessdate=2020-10-29|archive-date=2020-11-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201124041634/https://jimwatsonottawa.ca/en/about-jim/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

當時安省政府計劃改革[[安大略省行政區劃|省内行政區劃]]，當中包括將渥太華市與其周邊城鎮及其對上的渥太華－卡爾頓區合併成新的渥太華市；外界視合併後渥太華市的市長職位為沃森和時任渥太華－卡爾頓區主席薛雅禮（{{lang|en|Bob Chiarelli}}）之爭<ref name="Citizen121006"/>。在民調支持度落後薛雅禮的沃森於1999年宣布不會競逐合併後市長職位，並於其市長任期屆滿前於2000年8月提早離職，改任加拿大旅遊委員會總裁至2002年<ref name="Citizen121006"/><ref name="about"/>。他其後短暫重返傳媒業，主持渥太華CHRO電視台的午間新聞資訊節目，並每周為《渥太華公民報》撰寫專欄<ref name="Citizen121006"/><ref name="OLM"/>。

==轉投省政==
[[File:Jim_Watson,_MPP_(cropped).jpg|thumb]]

沃森於2003年安省省選中代表[[安大略自由黨|安省自由黨]]競逐[[安大略省議會|省議會]]渥太華西－尼皮安選區（{{lang|en|Ottawa West—Nepean}}）議席，以47%得票率擊敗尋求連任的[[安大略進步保守黨|進步保守黨]]候選人，首度出任省議員並獲[[安大略省省長|省長]][[道爾頓·麥堅迪|麥堅迪]]任命為消費者及商業事務廳長<ref name="Citizen121006"/><ref name="OLM"/>。他任内於2004年春季促成省府和聯邦政府達成協議，在省内多處由該兩級政府提供一站式服務以便省民；該協議其後延伸至市鎮級政府，居民自此可在渥太華市政廳等地獲取多項三級政府服務<ref>{{cite web|title=CANADA AND ONTARIO LAUNCH JOINT SERVICE DELIVERY STRATEGY, Working Together to Help Save Money and Provide Better Service to Citizens|url=https://www.canada.ca/en/news/archive/2004/05/canada-ontario-launch-joint-service-delivery-strategy-working-together-help-save-money-provide-better-service-citizens.html|publisher=Government of Canada|accessdate=23 January 2018|archive-date=2018-09-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180922135759/https://www.canada.ca/en/news/archive/2004/05/canada-ontario-launch-joint-service-delivery-strategy-working-together-help-save-money-provide-better-service-citizens.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

麥堅迪於2005年6月調動內閣，沃森改任首任衞生推廣廳長<ref name="Citizen121006"/><ref name="OLM"/>，任内省府於2006年5月通過《安大略免煙法案》，省内所有餐廳、酒吧和賭場等公眾場所自此全面禁煙<ref>{{cite web|title=Historic Smoke-Free Ontario Act is a joint effort|url=https://news.ontario.ca/archive/en/2006/05/18/Historic-SmokeFree-Ontario-Act-is-a-joint-effort.html|website=Government of Ontario|accessdate=23 January 2018|archive-date=2019-02-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190207020123/https://news.ontario.ca/archive/en/2006/05/18/Historic-SmokeFree-Ontario-Act-is-a-joint-effort.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

沃森於2007年省選連任渥太華西－尼皮安選區省議員，並獲麥堅迪任命為城鎮事務及房屋廳長<ref name="Citizen121006"/>。他於2008年2月引入項目資助省内低收入家庭在往後五年時期繳付租金<ref>{{cite web|title=Helping Households Pay Their Rent|url=https://news.ontario.ca/archive/en/2008/02/22/Helping-Households-Pay-Their-Rent.html|website=Government of Ontario|accessdate=23 January 2018|archive-date=2019-02-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190207015834/https://news.ontario.ca/archive/en/2008/02/22/Helping-Households-Pay-Their-Rent.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。同年10月省府從市鎮級政府接管部分事務，涉及金額約為15億元，以期舒緩市鎮級政府開支；牽涉範疇包括急救和公眾衞生事務、公共交通、殘疾支援項目、和物業税項評估等<ref>{{cite web|title=Ontario Municipal Partnership Fund 2008 – Minister's Memo|url=https://www.fin.gov.on.ca/en/budget/ompf/2008/mletter_mar08.html|website=Ontario Ministry of Finance|accessdate=23 January 2018|archive-date=2020-01-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200108051953/https://www.fin.gov.on.ca/en/budget/ompf/2008/mletter_mar08.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

==重回市府==
[[File:A11K0528.jpg|thumb]]

沃森於2010年1月12日宣布辭去省議員和廳長職務，並競逐同年10月舉行的渥太華市長選舉<ref>[https://ottawacitizen.com/Watson+running+mayor+Ottawa/2432341/story.html "Watson running to be mayor of Ottawa"]. ''Ottawa Citizen'', January 12, 2010.</ref><ref>{{cite news | url=https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/ottawa/mpp-watson-to-run-for-ottawa-mayor-1.894536 | work=CBC News | title=MPP Watson to run for Ottawa mayor | date=2010-01-12 | accessdate=2020-10-30 | archive-date=2017-03-09 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170309220353/http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/ottawa/mpp-watson-to-run-for-ottawa-mayor-1.894536 | dead-url=no }}</ref>；他最終以49%得票率贏取市長職位<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/ottawa/watson-wins-ottawa-mayor-s-race-1.905765 | work=CBC News | title=Watson wins Ottawa mayor's race | date=October 25, 2010 | accessdate=2020-10-30 | archive-date=2020-10-01 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201001063710/https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/ottawa/watson-wins-ottawa-mayor-s-race-1.905765 | dead-url=no }}</ref>。他重返市府後凍結自己的市長薪金，並削減市長辦公室預算10%<ref>"{{cite web |url=http://ottawa.ca/en/city-hall/budget-and-taxes/budget/budget-2011-highlights |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2013-01-12 |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130219192420/http://ottawa.ca/en/city-hall/budget-and-taxes/budget/budget-2011-highlights |archivedate=2013-02-19 |dead-url=no }}"</ref><ref>{{cite news| url=https://ottawacitizen.com/news/Watson+access+protocol+budget+renders+integrity+policy/7754443/story.html | work=Ottawa Citizen | title=Watson's access to protocol budget renders integrity policy opaque | date=December 28, 2012}}</ref>，又承諾物業稅增幅少於2.5%<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.ottawasun.com/2012/10/24/draft-budget-proposes-209-tax-hike | work=Ottawa Sun | title=Draft budget proposes 2.09% tax hike | date=October 24, 2012 | accessdate=2020-10-30 | archive-date=2016-03-04 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304053733/http://www.ottawasun.com/2012/10/24/draft-budget-proposes-209-tax-hike | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.ottawasun.com/2012/11/02/furey-ottawa-mayor-jim-watson-true-to-his-promises | work=Ottawa Sun | title=Ottawa mayor Jim Watson true to his promises | date=November 2, 2012 | accessdate=2020-10-30 | archive-date=2021-11-15 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211115161721/https://ottawasun.com/2012/11/02/furey-ottawa-mayor-jim-watson-true-to-his-promises }}</ref><ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.cbc.ca/ottawamorning/2012/10/25/mayor-watson | work=CBC News | title=Mayor Watson  | date=October 25, 2012}}</ref>。他引入一系列措施確保市府廉潔和透明運作，包括聘用操守專員、成立說客註冊表、以及規定市府民選人員需在市府網站公布開支記錄<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.ottawasun.com/2012/11/26/watson-reacts-to-ford-decision | work=Ottawa Sun | title=Watson reacts to Ford decision | date=November 26, 2012 | accessdate=2020-10-30 | archive-date=2016-03-04 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304040446/http://www.ottawasun.com/2012/11/26/watson-reacts-to-ford-decision | dead-url=no }}</ref>。他凍結市府社區康樂服務收費四年<ref>"{{cite web |url=http://ottawa.ca/en/budget-2013 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2013-01-12 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130121170439/http://ottawa.ca/en/budget-2013 |archivedate=2013-01-21 |dead-url=no }}"</ref>，並兩度裁減市府職員總數<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/ottawa/story/2011/10/26/ottawa-budget-city-hall-watson.html | work=CBC News | title=Draft budget sets Ottawa tax increase at 2.39% | date=October 26, 2011 | accessdate=2020-10-30 | archive-date=2011-10-27 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111027212840/http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/ottawa/story/2011/10/26/ottawa-budget-city-hall-watson.html | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.ottawasun.com/2012/10/24/sherring-2013-draft-budget-has-tidbits-for-everyone | work=Ottawa Sun | title=2013 draft budget has tidbits for everyone | date=October 24, 2012 | accessdate=2020-10-30 | archive-date=2021-11-15 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211115161735/https://ottawasun.com/2012/10/24/sherring-2013-draft-budget-has-tidbits-for-everyone }}</ref>，又促成渥太華投資推廣署<ref>{{cite web|title=Watson Campaign Announcement|url=https://ottawacitizen.com/news/local-news/live-at-230-jim-watson-makes-a-campaign-announcement|website=Ottawa Citizen|publisher=Michael Woods|accessdate=23 January 2018|archive-date=2018-01-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180109063809/http://ottawacitizen.com/news/local-news/live-at-230-jim-watson-makes-a-campaign-announcement|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

渥太華兩項耽誤多年的大型項目在沃森該屆市長任期得以落實<ref>{{cite news | url=https://ottawacitizen.com/news/Everyone+board/7758279/story.html | work=Ottawa Citizen | title=Most people are on board, so far | date=December 30, 2012 | accessdate=2020-10-30 | archive-date=2018-08-11 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180811032659/http://www.ottawacitizen.com/news/Everyone+board/7758279/story.html | dead-url=no }}</ref>：市議會於2012年10月通過蘭斯頓公園（{{lang|en|Lansdowne Park}}）振興項目<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/ottawa/story/2012/10/10/ottawa-lansdowne-waterfall-agreement.html | work=CBC News | title=Final Lansdowne deal passed by council | date=October 10, 2012 | accessdate=2020-10-30 | archive-date=2013-01-11 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130111093629/http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/ottawa/story/2012/10/10/ottawa-lansdowne-waterfall-agreement.html | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news | url=https://ottawacitizen.com/news/Council+gives+final+ahead+Lansdowne+project/7369051/story.html | work=Ottawa Citizen | title=Council gives final go ahead to Lansdowne project | date=October 11, 2012 | accessdate=2020-10-30 | archive-date=2019-07-05 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190705053632/http://www.ottawacitizen.com/news/Council+gives+final+ahead+Lansdowne+project/7369051/story.html | dead-url=no }}</ref>，再於同年12月一致通過興建[[渥太華輕鐵|渥太華輕鐵]][[聯邦線_(渥太華)|聯邦線]]<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/ottawa/story/2012/12/19/ottawa-lrt-approved-confederation-line-light-rail-council.html | work=CBC News | title=Confederation Line LRT project approved by council | date=December 19, 2012 | accessdate=2020-10-30 | archive-date=2013-05-29 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130529203355/http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/ottawa/story/2012/12/19/ottawa-lrt-approved-confederation-line-light-rail-council.html | dead-url=no }}</ref>。

沃森在2014年市選以76.20%得票率連任市長<ref>{{cite web|title=2014 Election Results|url=https://ottawa.ca/election/index_en.html|website=City of Ottawa|accessdate=23 January 2018|archive-date=2018-09-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180920045452/https://ottawa.ca/election/index_en.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。此後市府成功從聯邦政府獲取11億5千萬元撥款，讓聯邦線輕鐵繼續對外延伸<ref>{{cite web|title=Federal government commits to funding LRT Stage 2|url=http://ottawa.ctvnews.ca/federal-government-commits-to-funding-lrt-stage-2-1.3461290|website=CTV News Ottawa|accessdate=23 January 2018|archive-date=2020-05-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200502013744/https://ottawa.ctvnews.ca/federal-government-commits-to-funding-lrt-stage-2-1.3461290|dead-url=no}}</ref>。沃森又爭取渥太華和[[加蒂諾|加蒂諾]]兩市市長成為國家首都委員會（{{lang|en|National Capital Commission}}）成員；兩市市長終在2016年獲邀成為該委員會的[[官守議員|官守成員]]，但沒有投票權<ref>{{cite web|title=NCC board invites mayors of Ottawa and Gatineau to participate in meetings|url=https://ottawacitizen.com/news/local-news/ncc-board-invites-mayors-of-ottawa-and-gatineau-to-participate-in-meetings|website=Ottawa Citizen|accessdate=23 January 2018|archive-date=2018-01-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180111052752/http://ottawacitizen.com/news/local-news/ncc-board-invites-mayors-of-ottawa-and-gatineau-to-participate-in-meetings|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

2018年市選，沃森以71.03%得票率再度連任市長<ref>{{cite web|title=2018 Election Results|url=https://ottawa.ca/election/2018_en.html|website=City of Ottawa|accessdate=31 October 2018|archive-date=2019-05-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190505065610/https://ottawa.ca/election/2018_en.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

